# Deterministic thresholds for [eval]-tagged tasks — one metric per line:
#   name|command|comparator|threshold
# - `command` must print a single number (int or float) to stdout.
# - `comparator` is one of: >=  <=  >  <  ==
#
# NEVER invent plausible-sounding numbers here. These thresholds gate
# whether a task auto-commits-and-continues with no human review — only add
# a line once a human has actually decided what "good enough" means for
# that metric. Until then, leave this file with zero metric lines below;
# every [eval] task then correctly falls back to the human-gated path
# (gates/eval-judgment-checklist.md), same as [design]/[structural].
#
# Example (uncomment and edit with real numbers, or delete once real ones
# are added below):
# accuracy|python eval/run_accuracy.py|>=|0.85
# p95_latency_ms|python eval/run_latency.py|<=|400
# cost_per_call_usd|python eval/run_cost.py|<=|0.01
